'I have thirty with me,'
'But even as Aragorn they are courteous, if they break their silence.'
'Yes, the Dead ride behind. They have been summoned,'
'Where in Middle-earth are we?'
', and they are fair and gallant as Elven-lords; and that is not to be wondered at in the sons of Elrond of Rivendell.'
'We have descended from the uprising of the Morthond, the long chill river that flows at last to the sea that washes the walls of Dol Amroth. You will not need to ask hereafter how comes its name: Blackroot men call it.'
